I do not here profess to be a mere translator3 for I have widely other objects in view: yet not only have I very often translated with minute accuracy, but I have never introduced ornaments of my own. If any one unacquainted with the original should read my Latin, he must attribute whatever in it he finds of beauty to the genius of Mr. Longfellow.

The names of certain birds and beasts, as also a few things essentially modern, could not be expressed by Latin words found in the existing classics ε but that is of absolutely no importance, if only the new words be formed according to strict classical analogies. Nevertheless, it seems right to annex a short Glossary for the student's con- venience.
